name Coq au Riesling with Squash and Mushrooms
serves 5
note Goes well with roast potatoes, gnocchi, Spätzle, Schupfnudeln or baguette.
tags main, meat, french, autumn

# Mise en place

- 6 cloves garlic
Cut into thin slices.
-> garlic

- 250 g shallots
@nodep
Peel and quarter.
-> shallots

- 400 g squash
@nodep
Wash, deseed and cut into cubes.
-> squash

- 200 g dried plums
@nodep
Quarter.
-> plums

- 300 g mushrooms
@nodep
Clean and halve if large.
-> mushrooms

- 300 g grapes
@nodep
Halve.
-> grapes

# Preparation

- 1 kg chicken breast
- salt
- pepper
@nodep
Cut into large pieces, season with salt and pepper.
-> chicken

- 500 ml Riesling
- 200 ml chicken stock
- 1 tbsp tomato paste
- 4 sprigs thyme
- 3 sprigs rosemary
- 2 bay leaves
- oil
= chicken
= shallots
= garlic
Preheat the oven to 200°C. Heat oil in a casserole and brown the chicken with the
shallots, herbs and bay leaves on all sides. Stir in the tomato paste, pour in the wine
and stock and add the garlic. Place in the oven uncovered and braise for about 10 minutes.
-> casserole 1

= squash
@ casserole 1
Add the squash and cook for a further 30 minutes.
-> casserole 2

= plums
@ casserole 2
Add the plums and braise for a further 5 minutes.
-> casserole 3

- 50 g butter
= mushrooms
Melt the butter in a pan and fry the mushrooms until golden brown.
-> fried mushrooms

- 200 g chestnuts
- parsley
= fried mushrooms
= grapes
@ casserole 3
Add the mushrooms, chestnuts, grapes and parsley to the casserole, stir to combine and
season to taste.
